snippet.textDisplay: I know I'm a little late for anyone to see this, let alone MatPat. Eyes changing later in life may be rare, but it does happen. Particularly around puberty where there are all sorts of hormones in flux. I was born a bright blue and hazel eyed baby, but after puberty my eyes are distinctly  green hazel. Blue to green may not be a huge change on the color scale, but my eyes look completely different than they did as a child.
